CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 15, 1950, page 7, reads: "Won Shriners' Talent Hunt - These three women won prizes in talent hunt, staged by Prince Hall Shriners, Sahara Temple, at A. Leo Weil School on July 3. They will go to Boston to compete in national finals. Left to right: Kathleen N. Handy, singer, who won first place; Virginia Carter, Donora, pianist, second place, and Romayne Turner, singer, third place. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of three talent hunt winners, left to right: second place pianist Virginia Carter Donora holding trophy, first place singer Kathleen N. Handy holding trophy, and third place singer Romayne Turner holding plaque, posed beside steps of brick church
